LAGOS  – Falcon Aerospace Limited has launched two technology platforms designed to ease business jet booking and make access to the service more inclusive. The business aviation firm introduced the products at a recent event in Lagos where it unveiled its operational business units, Chukwuerika Achum, the CEO stated that Falcon Aerospace’s business model derives from the increased demand for business aviation by more Africans doing business across and outside Africa, and non-Africans flying into the continent for business and tourism. “We are proud of our African origin and are deeply committed to the continent’s development. As an organization with deep African roots and values, we possess a significant understanding of the business terrain in Africa,” said Achum. He added that the company’s obsession with innovation has led it to create products targeted at delivering more value to customers. “Operating through our business units, we aim to make a difference in an often exclusive and elusive market via the delivery of excellent customer service, adaptation of technology, inclusive customer targeting, and continuous innovation” Falcon Aerospace’s business units unveiled at the event are Vivajets, CharterXE and FlyPJX. ‒‒:‒‒/‒‒:‒‒ Vivajets a full business aviation company providing a wide range of services including charter brokerage, fractional ownership, Aircraft management, sales and leasing, consulting and training. POLL Vivajets is the company’s operational brand and will relate with regulators and other critical industry stakeholders to get the necessary permits, certifications and licenses for the group to operaCharterXE is an automated private jet booking platform that provides access to the company’s charter brokerage services through digital devices. Available as a mobile app and also via web, CharterXE leverages cutting edge technological innovation to cut through all the physical hassles involved in booking a private jet.